// Captured #withGalaxy S9 produced with @samsungmobileusa using Pro mode ISO 50 at 1/120th f 2.4
The sun sets of the Pungwe River in Mozambique. The Pungwe rises in Zimbabwe below Mount Nyangani and then flows into Mozambique where it enters the Rift Valley and forms the southern boundary of Gorongosa National Park. When I took this shot the sounds of people singing in the villages along the river valley made for a pretty magical experience.
